==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dalles
<hw>Dalles</hw> <pr>(d⟦acr⟧lz)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>dalle</ets> a tube, gutter, trough.]</ety> <def>A rapid, esp. one
where the channel is narrowed between rock walls.</def>
<mark>[Northwestern U. S. & Canada]</mark></p>

<p><q>The place below, where the compressed river wound like a silver
thread among the flat black rocks, was the far-famed <qex>Dalles</qex>
of the Columbia.</q> <rj><qau>F. H. Balch.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dalliance</ent>⟦br⟧
